{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who embezzled a relatively modest sum and has demonstrated remorse through partial restitution. While embezzlement is a serious breach of fiduciary duty, a ten-year sentence as suggested by the spectator is disproportionate to the scale of the crime and the defendant's lack of a prior record. A custodial sentence of 6 months is sufficient to address the criminality of the act while allowing for rehabilitation and further efforts toward full restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
